article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 82, Cleveland St. 75
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Anthony Hill and Ja'Rob McCallum scored 14 points apiece as Wisconsin-Milwaukee beat Cleveland State 82-75 Friday night in the second round of the Horizon League tournament. Ricky Franklin added 13, Ryan Haggerty 12, James Eayrs 11 and Jason Haverkamp 10 for the fourth-seeded Panthers (20-13), who have won seven of their last eight. Wisconsin-Milwaukee will face top seed Butler (26-4) in the semifinals Saturday. Tim Kamczyc scored 20 to lead the fifth-seeded Vikings (21-12), who won last year's tournament. Norris Cole added 16, Jeremy Montgomery 15 and Lance James 13. Wisconsin-Milwaukee shot 55.3 percent (26 of 47) from the field and 57.1 percent (8 of 14) from 3-point territory. The Panthers never trailed. Wisconsin-Milwaukee, which won its 20th game for the second time in coach Rob Jeter's five seasons, opened the tournament with a 73-67 victory over Illinois-Chicago.
